  "body": "The 2.0.1 version broke the `--values` flag of the `upgrade` command. When I use a values file it returns the following error:\r\n`Error: failed to parse configs.yml: error unmarshaling JSON: json: Unmarshal(non-pointer map[string]interface {})`\r\n\r\nThe problem is with Unmarshal on [line 174 of the upgrade.go file](../blob/master/cmd/helm/upgrade.go#L174) The 2nd argument needs to be a pointer.\r\n\r\nThe line should be `if err := yaml.Unmarshal(bytes, &base); err != nil {`",
